Successfully updated MCP n8n server for NPM distribution:

COMPLETED CHANGES:
1. Updated src/index.ts: Removed dependency on ~/.mcp-n8n/config.json, now uses ONLY environment variables N8N_BASE_URL (defaults to http://localhost:5678) and N8N_API_KEY (required)
2. Updated bin/setup.js: Now generates claude_mcp.json configuration with environment variables instead of saving to ~/.mcp-n8n/config.json
3. Updated package.json: Fixed bin entry for NPX compatibility
4. Tested successfully: Server starts with env vars, fails properly without API key, config generation works

RESULT: Users can now configure with:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "n8n": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@ken8n/mcp-n8n"],
      "env": {
        "N8N_BASE_URL": "https://their-n8n.com",
        "N8N_API_KEY": "their-api-key-here"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Ken8n-coder MCP setup requirements analyzed:

1. CLI Structure: Uses yargs with commands in packages/ken8n-coder/src/cli/cmd/
2. Existing MCP command: Already has McpCommand with "add" subcommand for generic MCP servers
3. Configuration: ken8n-coder.json has MCP section with n8n entry already configured
4. N8n MCP needs: N8N_BASE_URL and N8N_API_KEY environment variables
5. Package: @kenkaiii/ken8n-mcp is the MCP server package
6. N8n Client: Has comprehensive API client with testConnection() method for validation
7. Config system: Uses config/config.ts with Zod schemas for validation and supports {env:VAR} syntax

Current n8n MCP config format:
```json
{
  "mcp": {
    "n8n": {
      "type": "local",
      "command": ["npx", "@kenkaiii/ken8n-mcp"],
      "environment": {
        "N8N_BASE_URL": "{env:N8N_BASE_URL}",
        "N8N_API_KEY": "{env:N8N_API_KEY}"
      },
      "enabled": true
    }
  }
}
```
